Tidy methods for fdm and asym models

Source: R/asym.R, R/diffs.R
fdm_tidiers.Rd

panelr provides methods to access fdm and asym data in a tidy format

# S3 method for asym
tidy(x, conf.int = FALSE, conf.level = 0.95, ...)

# S3 method for fdm
tidy(x, conf.int = FALSE, conf.level = 0.95, ...)

# S3 method for fdm
glance(x, ...)

Arguments

x

An fdm or asym object.

conf.int

Logical indicating whether or not to include a confidence interval in the tidied output. Defaults to FALSE.

conf.level

The confidence level to use for the confidence interval if conf.int = TRUE. Must be strictly greater than 0 and less than 1. Defaults to 0.95, which corresponds to a 95 percent confidence interval.

...

Ignored

Examples


data("WageData")
wages <- panel_data(WageData, id = id, wave = t)
model <- fdm(lwage ~ wks + union, data = wages)
if (requireNamespace("generics")) {
  generics::tidy(model)
}
#> # A tibble: 3 × 5
#>   estimate std.error statistic   p.value term

#> 3 0.0199    0.0221       0.904 3.67e-  1 union
